I wanted to verify.

46:54.683 --> 46:56.099
I can answer your questions.

46:58.224 --> 47:00.349
Uh, okay, well...

47:01.140 --> 47:03.641
I did the math,
and it looks like the SkyWalk

47:03.724 --> 47:06.307
is gonna end up costing
around eight million dollars.

47:06.391 --> 47:08.140
-Seven-five, sure.
-Right.

47:08.224 --> 47:10.432
It just seems like
a lot of our resources

47:10.516 --> 47:12.265
to be spending on cosmetics.

47:13.391 --> 47:16.599
Cosmetics?
People love the SkyWalk.

47:16.683 --> 47:18.182
"The Beacon" loves the SkyWalk.

47:18.265 --> 47:19.974
There was that nice poll
you guys did.

47:20.057 --> 47:21.349
Right.

47:21.432 --> 47:23.974
But the ceilings at the
high school are still leaking.

47:24.057 --> 47:26.057
I mean, some of the classrooms
had to get shut down.

47:26.140 --> 47:27.140
Sounds like you
should bring that up

47:27.224 --> 47:29.057
with your
student government.

47:31.557 --> 47:33.140
There was also
the pizza oven.

47:34.224 --> 47:36.182
-What?
-I saw a line item

47:36.265 --> 47:38.808
in the expense reports
for a pizza oven.

47:39.140 --> 47:40.766
But then I asked Paula
in the cafeteria

47:40.849 --> 47:42.349
and she said she knew
nothing about it.

47:42.432 --> 47:43.641
Just stop it.

47:48.307 --> 47:50.265
I am sorry to be the one
to tell you this,

47:50.349 --> 47:52.933
but no one is keeping
anything from you, okay?

47:53.015 --> 47:55.683
On the contrary,
we come in here every day

47:55.766 --> 47:58.140
at the crack of dawn
because we care.

47:58.599 --> 47:59.974
We care about providing you

48:00.057 --> 48:03.557
with a proper quality education
because we're good people.

48:03.933 --> 48:06.182
Because we want you
to have a good life.

48:06.265 --> 48:07.599
Okay?

48:09.641 --> 48:10.808
Okay.

48:11.265 --> 48:12.391
Pam: Okay.

48:14.641 --> 48:17.808
The individual purchase orders
are still public record, though.

48:21.933 --> 48:23.182
(chuckles)

48:24.474 --> 48:26.099
(opens drawer)

48:26.182 --> 48:27.516
Pam: Here you go.

48:29.641 --> 48:31.265
-Thank you.
-Mm-hmm.

48:31.974 --> 48:33.057
Oh, and Rachel.

48:33.140 --> 48:35.224
You were right about
that pizza oven.

48:35.557 --> 48:37.140
It didn't go
to the high school

48:37.474 --> 48:39.432
because we bought it
for the middle school.

48:39.974 --> 48:42.391
Yeah, they have pizza
for days down there.

48:42.474 --> 48:43.808
Go get yourself a slice.

48:50.307 --> 48:51.224
Frank: Morning.

48:51.307 --> 48:52.933
-Hi.
-Oh, hey, Rachel.

48:54.140 --> 48:57.182
Dr. Tassone, Pam Gluckin's
in a bit of a state.

48:57.265 --> 48:58.849
Yeah, I have a very
busy morning.

48:58.933 --> 49:00.683
Just tell her I can't.
Good morning.

49:01.516 --> 49:04.015
Pam:
Frank, Frank, Frank!

49:04.099 --> 49:05.057
Fra--

49:06.766 --> 49:07.891
(door closes)

49:10.724 --> 49:12.391
I'm sorry, Dr. Tassone's
very busy this morning.

49:12.474 --> 49:13.474
Get out of my way, Mary Ann.

49:13.557 --> 49:15.140
-Pam, Pam.
-Please.

49:16.349 --> 49:18.015
You know what?
It's fine.

49:21.099 --> 49:22.182
Everything's fine.

49:44.099 --> 49:45.891
My exit interview for him.

49:53.265 --> 49:54.599
(knock on door)

49:55.307 --> 49:56.808
-Hey.
-Jenny: Hey, Dr. Tassone.

49:56.891 --> 49:59.140
Uh, Mary Ann said
you wanted to see me?

49:59.224 --> 50:01.599
Frank: Yes, yes.
Uh, take a seat.

50:01.683 --> 50:03.557
Just close the door
behind you there.

50:08.933 --> 50:11.307
So, I think maybe

50:11.391 --> 50:14.265
it is time that we talked
about your value

50:14.349 --> 50:15.891
in this workplace.

50:18.849 --> 50:21.140
I, uh...

50:21.474 --> 50:23.391
-This isn't...
-No, rest assured,

50:23.474 --> 50:25.933
we all want you
to succeed here.

50:26.766 --> 50:28.599
Which is--
(clears throat)

50:28.683 --> 50:32.683
Which is why we would like
to transition you

50:32.933 --> 50:35.224
to our special utilities
department.

50:36.808 --> 50:38.099
Oh.

50:38.599 --> 50:40.140
Sir, um...

50:40.224 --> 50:43.265
you know, I just thought I was
a really good fit up here.

50:43.349 --> 50:45.849
Oh, yeah, no, no, no.
We're just doing some shuffling

50:45.933 --> 50:48.265
and we could really use
an extra hand down there.

50:48.599 --> 50:49.891
Okay?

50:51.516 --> 50:54.432
What about Pam's old job?
You know, I thought maybe, uh,

50:54.516 --> 50:56.516
you know, like a manager,
maybe I could be--

50:56.599 --> 50:58.140
Maybe I could be right for that.

50:58.224 --> 50:59.641
Yeah, well, actually,
Philip Metzger's

50:59.724 --> 51:02.516
gonna be stepping in as
the interim business manager.

51:02.974 --> 51:04.557
-Phil the auditor?
-Yeah, yeah.

51:04.641 --> 51:07.599
I mean, until we can find
a more permanent
replacement for Pam.

51:07.683 --> 51:09.099
But...

51:09.808 --> 51:11.182
we're pretty excited about him.

51:15.599 --> 51:18.265
I think that I should, uh...

51:19.849 --> 51:21.307
think, um...

51:25.265 --> 51:28.599
I know what
you all did to Pam.

51:30.516 --> 51:32.516
And I could,
you know, I could...

51:33.432 --> 51:35.808
maybe tell people.

51:35.891 --> 51:38.391
Frank:
Sorry, hold on a second.
I'm so sorry to interrupt.

51:38.474 --> 51:41.391
I just noticed that necklace
you have on.

51:41.474 --> 51:43.974
How it really
complements your eyes.

51:45.099 --> 51:46.891
-Thank you.
-It's, uh,

51:46.974 --> 51:48.391
yeah, that's,
that's new, isn't it?

51:48.474 --> 51:50.849
I don't think I've seen you
wearing it around before.

51:52.307 --> 51:54.766
Yeah, I thought so.
Yeah. I've got...

51:54.849 --> 51:57.099
I got sort of an eye for
these things, I don't know.

51:57.182 --> 51:58.808
So, um, what do you think?

51:58.891 --> 52:01.516
Is that-- is that
a Macy's purchase
or are we talking

52:01.599 --> 52:03.307
Lord & Taylor collection?

52:10.015 --> 52:11.766
Special utilities,
you said?

52:12.015 --> 52:14.015
Yeah, I think so.

52:15.808 --> 52:17.474
Okay, thanks, Jen.

52:21.641 --> 52:23.224
(door opens)

52:30.683 --> 52:32.015
(chuckles)

52:32.099 --> 52:33.516
(paper crumples)

52:37.974 --> 52:40.724
Mary Ann, can I get a cup
of that new coffee in here?

52:45.599 --> 52:46.891
(doorbell rings)

52:49.683 --> 52:50.933
Amber:
Oh, Rocco, you're so annoying.

52:51.015 --> 52:52.015
Get out of the way.

52:52.724 --> 52:54.182
Go.

53:05.766 --> 53:07.516
-Mom!
-Pam: This is she.

53:07.599 --> 53:09.099
(woman on phone, indistinct)

53:09.182 --> 53:10.265
No.

53:10.933 --> 53:12.015
Wait, what?

53:12.391 --> 53:15.557
Yeah, thank you.
Please don't call here again.

53:15.641 --> 53:17.015
-Who was that?
-That was a student.

53:17.099 --> 53:18.766
They want to donate
the fashion show proceeds

53:18.849 --> 53:21.015
to help pay for
my medical expenses.

53:21.557 --> 53:23.015
-But you're not sick.
-Don't eat that.

53:23.099 --> 53:24.099
We're returning them.

53:24.182 --> 53:26.599
Pam, what the hell
is going on?

53:29.557 --> 53:31.307
Bob: Okay, uh...

53:31.391 --> 53:33.057
first off, we want
to take a moment

53:33.140 --> 53:34.974
to acknowledge Pamela Gluckin.

53:35.599 --> 53:38.516
Uh, our hearts go out to her
and her entire family

53:38.599 --> 53:41.557
and we wish her a safe
and speedy recovery, yeah.

53:44.140 --> 53:46.182
Okay, all right, now.

53:46.265 --> 53:47.599
Onto the fun stuff.

53:49.391 --> 53:51.015
Look at these numbers, folks.

53:51.557 --> 53:54.015
These are the best
early decision numbers

53:54.099 --> 53:55.974
that we've ever seen.

53:56.432 --> 53:57.557
Yeah.

53:57.641 --> 53:59.474
Give yourselves
a round of applause.

54:02.599 --> 54:06.474
♪ I'll have a blue ♪

54:06.974 --> 54:08.766
♪ Christmas ♪

54:09.599 --> 54:11.516
♪ Without you ♪

54:12.974 --> 54:16.265
♪ I'll be so blue ♪

54:17.349 --> 54:21.474
♪ Just thinking about you ♪

54:24.474 --> 54:29.557
♪ Decorations of red ♪

54:29.641 --> 54:33.683
♪ On a green Christmas tree ♪

54:36.099 --> 54:39.891
♪ Won't be the same, dear ♪

54:39.974 --> 54:43.808
♪ If you're not here with me ♪

54:43.891 --> 54:48.516
♪ And when those blue ♪

54:48.599 --> 54:52.474
♪ Snowflakes start falling ♪

54:54.182 --> 54:58.432
♪ That's when those blue ♪

54:58.516 --> 55:02.641
♪ Memories start falling ♪

55:05.307 --> 55:09.391
♪ You'll be doing all right ♪

55:10.432 --> 55:14.599
♪ With your
Christmas of white ♪

55:15.891 --> 55:18.140
♪ But I'll ♪

55:18.224 --> 55:19.391
♪ Have a blue ♪

55:19.474 --> 55:20.391
Seven.

55:20.474 --> 55:22.307
♪ Blue, blue, blue Christmas ♪

55:22.391 --> 55:23.933
Six.

55:25.891 --> 55:27.224
Five.

55:46.432 --> 55:48.391
Hey, Rachel, um,
where's the article

55:48.474 --> 55:50.391
on the
Cancer Benefit Fashion Show?

55:50.849 --> 55:52.766
I'll get that
to you tomorrow.

55:53.182 --> 55:54.766
But we go to print tomorrow.

55:55.391 --> 55:56.933
Okay, I'll have it tonight.

55:57.766 --> 55:59.557
Look, if you wanna be
a part of the paper,

55:59.641 --> 56:01.391
you gotta be a part
of the paper.

56:01.474 --> 56:03.015
Look, I'm gonna be late.

56:03.099 --> 56:04.599
Rachel. Rachel!

56:04.683 --> 56:06.224
(binder clatters)

56:06.766 --> 56:08.015
-Shit.
-Oh, my God.

56:08.099 --> 56:10.474
-Sorry, shit.
-Seriously?

56:14.933 --> 56:16.224
What is this?

56:16.307 --> 56:19.766
It's just a personal project.
None of your business.

56:24.265 --> 56:26.391
Look, I'm sorry
for being a hard-ass.

56:26.766 --> 56:28.808
I know you're going through
a lot at home.

56:28.891 --> 56:30.391
What's that supposed to mean?

56:31.766 --> 56:33.891
You know, just everything
with your dad.

56:34.599 --> 56:36.099
Yeah, what about him?

56:37.891 --> 56:39.891
I mean, the parents
talk to each other.

56:39.974 --> 56:42.641
I know that some shit
happened at work.

56:44.099 --> 56:45.432
You don't know anything.

56:45.724 --> 56:47.849
Ow.
Fuck, Rachel.

56:49.307 --> 56:51.307
(pop music playing on radio)

56:51.391 --> 56:53.516
(paper rustling)

57:13.808 --> 57:15.849
-(knocking)
-David: Rach?

57:17.057 --> 57:18.516
-Dinner.
-Okay.

57:20.599 --> 57:21.724
What's all this?

57:22.349 --> 57:24.015
Uh, research.

57:24.099 --> 57:26.849
These are invoices
from the school district.

57:34.683 --> 57:36.015
(chuckles)

57:36.099 --> 57:38.349
The school district invoiced
over a million dollars

57:38.432 --> 57:39.808
in lab equipment?

57:41.391 --> 57:42.891
And that's just one supplier.

57:43.766 --> 57:44.849
(chuckles)

57:46.391 --> 57:48.349
You thought about
calling this company?

57:52.307 --> 57:54.516
(television playing, indistinct)

58:00.933 --> 58:02.766
Oh, God, I'm gonna
miss my flight.

58:03.182 --> 58:04.974
Not if you stay another day.

58:05.224 --> 58:06.933
You know I can't do that.

58:07.015 --> 58:08.391
(groans)

58:10.140 --> 58:11.849
You could get a job here.

58:13.641 --> 58:15.641
There are schools
in Clark County.

58:15.724 --> 58:17.057
Sure, but good ones?

58:18.140 --> 58:20.015
Was Roslyn any good
before you?

58:29.933 --> 58:33.307
Hi, is this Champion Products
in Uniondale?

58:33.391 --> 58:35.307
-Man (on phone): Yes, it is.
-Hi, my name is Rachel.

58:35.391 --> 58:36.974
I was just hoping to ask you
about a series of charges.

58:37.057 --> 58:38.349
Okay, yes, yes.
Thank you for
verifying, Felice.

58:38.432 --> 58:39.641
You've been a huge help.

58:39.724 --> 58:41.599
-Yeah.
-Thank you, bye-bye.

58:42.974 --> 58:44.224
That's right.

58:46.224 --> 58:47.432
Yeah, I can hold.

58:51.599 --> 58:53.599
(phone rings)

58:56.432 --> 58:59.265
Howard:
Bellmore Fine Auto,
this is Howard.

59:00.349 --> 59:03.557
Uh, I'm sorry.
Bellmore Fine Auto?

59:03.641 --> 59:07.641
I had this number listed
as an H.G. Consulting.

59:24.182 --> 59:25.766
Pam: Hi.

59:26.974 --> 59:28.140
What's the matter?

59:28.516 --> 59:31.599
Oh, nothing,
I'm just, just tired.

59:32.349 --> 59:33.933
I'll take those invoices.

59:43.224 --> 59:45.891
David:
Next up is WordPower Tech.

59:46.474 --> 59:49.599
Now, they billed
the school district $800,000

59:49.683 --> 59:51.724
but no one has any idea
who they are.

59:51.808 --> 59:53.015
And they're consistent.

59:53.099 --> 59:55.182
They've billed every year
for the past ten.

59:55.265 --> 59:57.849
Yeah, the company's registered
to Thomas Tuggiero

59:57.933 --> 59:59.391
with an address in Manhattan.

59:59.474 --> 01:00:01.891
I tried calling but the number
is disconnected.

01:00:02.224 --> 01:00:04.474
We're gonna leave that one
a question mark for right now

01:00:04.557 --> 01:00:08.265
because the next one I've got
is Porto Office Supplies.

01:00:08.349 --> 01:00:10.849
Now, I can't find any...

01:00:10.933 --> 01:00:13.057
(train rumbling)

01:00:26.391 --> 01:00:28.182
(whistle tweets)

01:01:22.766 --> 01:01:24.724
Man:
What, did you forget your key?

01:01:26.599 --> 01:01:27.766
Oh.

01:01:28.432 --> 01:01:29.641
Hello.

01:01:33.557 --> 01:01:35.099
Can I help you with something?

01:01:35.599 --> 01:01:36.766
Is this...

01:01:38.766 --> 01:01:40.432
Uh, I'm...

01:01:40.849 --> 01:01:41.974
I'm canvassing.

01:01:42.849 --> 01:01:44.099
For who?

01:01:48.516 --> 01:01:50.599
Oh, um, it's...

01:01:50.933 --> 01:01:52.891
I'm, I have the wrong apartment.

01:01:52.974 --> 01:01:54.140
(scoffs)

01:02:06.933 --> 01:02:08.474
(elevator bell dings)

01:02:35.641 --> 01:02:36.808
(door closes)

01:02:39.974 --> 01:02:41.683
You're back.

01:02:41.766 --> 01:02:44.307
I'm back.
Hey, thanks.

01:02:47.474 --> 01:02:48.683
Hey, what's for dinner?

01:02:49.265 --> 01:02:50.724
Salmon.

01:03:00.015 --> 01:03:01.641
What's the matter?

01:03:03.182 --> 01:03:05.182
Oh, it's just work.
Sorry.

01:03:06.849 --> 01:03:08.891
The salmon's a little dry.

01:03:09.974 --> 01:03:11.224
It's great.

01:03:12.891 --> 01:03:14.641
I can tell when you're lying.

01:03:20.057 --> 01:03:21.265
A little dry, maybe.

01:03:21.349 --> 01:03:23.140
The couscous, though,
is a small masterpiece.

01:03:23.224 --> 01:03:25.057
Oh, well, thank you very much.

01:03:25.516 --> 01:03:26.683
(chuckles)

01:03:31.182 --> 01:03:32.391
How was Omaha?

01:03:33.057 --> 01:03:35.849
Mm, dull.
Dull as all hell.

01:03:38.891 --> 01:03:40.140
So...

01:03:40.849 --> 01:03:43.474
So I'm sitting there
sandwiched between
Doug and Joe

01:03:43.557 --> 01:03:45.766
and there's no A/C
in the conference center

01:03:45.849 --> 01:03:47.808
so you can imagine
the smell while they...

01:03:47.891 --> 01:03:50.224
-Oh, God.
-...talked for hours

01:03:50.307 --> 01:03:54.307
about STEM programs
and state aid.

01:03:54.391 --> 01:03:55.849
It was, oh, yeah.

01:03:55.933 --> 01:03:58.891
-It was, it was a riot.
-Oh, sounds like a nightmare.

01:04:01.891 --> 01:04:03.474
Maybe I'll come along next time.

01:04:03.557 --> 01:04:05.182
(chuckles)

01:04:05.724 --> 01:04:07.099
As a buffer.

01:04:10.224 --> 01:04:11.891
I would never
subject you to that.

01:04:15.933 --> 01:04:18.432
(Tom humming)

01:04:48.307 --> 01:04:50.432
(quiet chatter)

01:04:52.599 --> 01:04:54.974
Okay, you have documents
to back this up?

01:04:55.307 --> 01:04:57.557
Years' worth of supposed
payments to vendors

01:04:57.641 --> 01:04:59.891
and confirmation
they were never received.

01:05:00.182 --> 01:05:02.057
Some of these companies,
they don't even exist.

01:05:02.140 --> 01:05:03.766
Well, no, you don't know that.

01:05:04.140 --> 01:05:06.557
I mean, you know
that for sure, right?

01:05:06.641 --> 01:05:07.849
WordPower Tech.

01:05:07.933 --> 01:05:09.641
They've billed the district
almost a million dollars

01:05:09.724 --> 01:05:11.307
and no one knows anything.

01:05:11.808 --> 01:05:13.057
-Because it isn't anything.
-Okay.

01:05:13.140 --> 01:05:14.766
It is a private apartment
on the upper East Side.

01:05:14.849 --> 01:05:16.849
-Yes, but that doesn't...
-And our superintendent

01:05:16.933 --> 01:05:18.974
-has the key.
-...necessarily
mean that it's fake.

01:05:21.140 --> 01:05:22.641
Come on, Nick,
you know what this is.

01:05:22.724 --> 01:05:25.224
If he hasn't reported this,
it's fraud.

01:05:25.307 --> 01:05:27.516
He's writing my college
recommendation letter.

01:05:32.265 --> 01:05:34.849
Fuck, fuck, god damn it.

01:05:35.641 --> 01:05:37.849
What are we even
talking about right now?

01:05:39.891 --> 01:05:43.015
Are you sure?
Are you sure, sure, sure

01:05:43.099 --> 01:05:44.683
you actually wanna do this?

01:05:48.015 --> 01:05:50.307
(quietly reading)

01:06:16.057 --> 01:06:17.474
Frank:
Mind if I join you?

01:06:27.641 --> 01:06:29.224
(exhales)

01:06:30.724 --> 01:06:31.974
Don't ever let a doctor find out

01:06:32.057 --> 01:06:33.683
you have high
cholesterol, Rachel.

01:06:33.766 --> 01:06:35.891
They'll make you do
the most horrible things.

01:06:40.432 --> 01:06:41.557
So.

01:06:42.557 --> 01:06:43.766
About yesterday.

01:06:44.557 --> 01:06:46.015
Yeah, uh...

01:06:47.307 --> 01:06:49.224
-That was--
-What were you doing there?

01:06:51.099 --> 01:06:52.349
I'm not upset.

01:06:52.432 --> 01:06:55.224
But it is very important
that you be honest.

01:06:57.307 --> 01:07:00.307
I was following up
on the listed address

01:07:00.391 --> 01:07:01.974
for a school contractor.

01:07:03.391 --> 01:07:04.766
Why were you doing that?

01:07:06.432 --> 01:07:08.349
It's public record.
Anyone could take the time--

01:07:08.432 --> 01:07:10.015
I didn't ask you
if it was public record.

01:07:10.099 --> 01:07:11.808
I-- I just asked you why.

01:07:15.808 --> 01:07:17.474
It's for something I'm writing.

01:07:19.766 --> 01:07:21.265
(exhales)

01:07:25.432 --> 01:07:27.182
I think you have real potential.

01:07:27.265 --> 01:07:29.265
-Dr. Tassone--
-No, I'm serious.

01:07:29.349 --> 01:07:31.474
I, I read all your bylines.

01:07:31.557 --> 01:07:33.474
You've come such a long way
since past September.

01:07:33.557 --> 01:07:35.724
Your confidence,
strength of ability.

01:07:35.933 --> 01:07:37.474
-Thank you.
-No, you have a tremendous

01:07:37.557 --> 01:07:39.099
future ahead of you,
Rachel, you do.

